<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-05T23:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-05T23:36:00-05:00" n="629" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17760</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Representative <persName type="from">Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Querétaro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-05T22:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1916, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>26. In relation to Northwestern Railway. Although, after long conference
                            early this morning, promised reply to-day, none has been forthcoming.
                            Appears deliberate evasion. Think instructions as requested and promised
                            will issue finally, but present attitude very unsatisfactory. This
                            morning was asked for names of consignees supplies. This evidently for
                            purpose of delay. Informed them would not ask for names, our agreement
                            being observed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rodgers</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>